001package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.insertion;
002
003/**
004 * Defines the contract for inserting data into UI components.
005 *
006 * <p>This interface is responsible for processing objects and mapping their values to UI components.
007 * Implementing classes should extract field values and perform the necessary UI interactions.
008 *
009 * <p>Typically, this service is used in test automation to dynamically insert data into forms,
010 * tables, or other interactive UI elements based on annotated fields in a data object.
011 *
012 * @author Cyborg Code Syndicate üíçüë®üíª
013 */
014public interface InsertionService {
015
016   /**
017    * Inserts data into UI components based on the provided object.
018    *
019    * <p>Implementations should:
020    * <ul>
021    *     <li>Extract field values from the given object.</li>
022    *     <li>Map each field to a corresponding UI component.</li>
023    *     <li>Use an appropriate insertion strategy to input the data.</li>
024    * </ul>
025    *
026    * @param data The object containing values to be inserted into UI components.
027    *             The fields should be properly annotated for mapping to UI elements.
028    */
029   void insertData(Object data);
030}
